{
  "text": "Some institutional authors [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] have argued that exceeding minimum requirements may also confer legitimacy, so that \"once minimal standards are met, corporations are likely to continue working\u2026 to be the best or the most admired\" (Staw and Epstein, 2000, p. 526) and that the firm's constituents prefer more substantive responses [CITATION_4] .",
